Perl6 <i>pointy block</i> is just a synonym for a function.  So below is exactly same as my <i>pointy block</i> example...<p><pre><code>  my $x = sub ($a, $b) { $a + $b };
</code></pre>
And typically with Perl TIMTOWTDI :)<p><pre><code>  my $x = -> { $^a + $^b };
</code></pre>
Personally I prefer the <i>pointy block</i> especially how it (visually) fits in with other Perl6 syntax constructs, for eg:<p><pre><code>  for 1..10 -> $odd, $even { say "odd $odd, even $even" }</code></pre>
